    <!-- Add insight / key takeaway directly related to activity / learner experience -->

    <!-- <insight>
    </insight> -->
    <insight>
        <p>
            From the learner experience we can get the amount by 
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol marker="(a)">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Amount after year <m>1</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow>110,000 = \amp \; 100,000 + 10,000 </mrow>
                            <mrow> = \amp \; 100,000\left(1 + 0.1\right) </mrow>
                            <mrow> = \amp \; 100,000 \left( 1 + \frac{10}{100}\right) </mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Amount after <m>2</m> years
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Notice that here our <m>P =\; \text{Ksh}\;110,000</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow>\text{Interest} \; =\amp \; \frac{R}{100} \times P </mrow>
                            <mrow> I = \amp \; \frac{10}{100}\times 100,000\left(1 + \frac{10}{100}\right) </mrow>
                            <mrow> A = \amp \; P + I </mrow>
                            <mrow> = \amp \; 100,000 \left(1 + \frac{10}{100}\right) +  \frac{10}{100}\times 100,000\left(1 + \frac{10}{100}\right) </mrow>
                            <mrow> = \amp \; 100,000 \left(1 + \frac{10}{100}\right) \left(1 + \frac{10}{100}\right) </mrow>
                            <mrow> 121,000 = \amp \;100,000 \left(1 + \frac{10}{100}\right)^2  </mrow>
                        </md>
                        
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        What is the amount after <m>3,4,5</m> years?
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p>
            The general formula for Compound interest is therefore;
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow> A = \amp \; P \left( 1 + \frac{R}{100}\right) ^ T </mrow>
                <mrow> CI = \amp \; A - P </mrow>
            </md>
            where
            <ol marker="(i)">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>A</m> is the amount,
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>P</m> is the principal,
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>R</m> is the rate,
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>T</m> is the time in years,
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
            
        </p>
    </insight>

    <!-- Add further instruction (not in a block) to develop ideas as needed -->

    <xi:include href="../lesson-plan-templates/example-intro.ptx" />

    <!-- Add at least 3 examples -->

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
              Onyimbo invest Ksh <m>3,000</m> in an investment account paying <m>3 \%</m> interest compounded quarterly, how much will the account be worth in <m>10</m> years?  
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Because we are starting with Ksh <m>3,000</m>, <m>P=3000.</m> Our interest rate is <m>3 \%</m>, so <m>r=0.03.</m> Because we are compounding quarterly, we are compounding <m>4</m> times per year, so <m>n=4.</m> We want to know the value of the account in <m>10</m> years, so we are looking for <m>A(10),</m> the value when <m>t=10.</m>
            </p>
            <p>
            <md>
                <mrow>A(t) &amp; =P\left(1+\frac{r}{n}\right)^{nt}</mrow>
                <mrow>A(10) &amp; =3000\left(1+\frac{0.03}{4}\right)^{4⋅10} </mrow>
                <mrow>≈\text{Ksh} \;4045.05 &amp; \text{ Round to two decimal places }.</mrow>
            </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                The account will be worth about Ksh <m>4,045.05</m> in 10 years.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A <m>529</m> Plan is a college-savings plan that allows relatives to invest money to pay for a child's future college tuition; the account grows tax-free. Lily wants to set up a <m>529</m> account for her new granddaughter and wants the account to grow to Ksh <m>400,000</m> over <m>18</m> years. The account earns <m>6</m> % compounded semi-annually. To the nearest Ksh, how much will Lily need to invest in the account now?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                The nominal interest rate is <m>6 \%</m>, so <m>r=0.06.</m> Interest is compounded twice a year, so <m>n=2.</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                We want to find the initial investment, <m>P,</m> needed so that the value of the account will be worth Ksh <m>400,000</m> in <m>18</m> years. Substitute the given values into the compound interest formula, and solve for <m>P.</m>
            </p>
            <p>
            <md>
                <mrow>A(t) &amp; =P\left(1+\frac{r}{n}\right)^{nt} </mrow>
                <mrow>400,000 &amp; =P\left(1+\frac{0.06}{2}\right)^{2(18)} </mrow>
                <mrow>400,000 &amp; =P(1.03)^{36}</mrow>
                <mrow>\frac{400,000}{(1.03)^{36}} &amp; = P </mrow>
                <mrow>P &amp; ≈\text{Ksh}\;138,010 </mrow>
            </md>
            </p>
            <p>Lily will need to invest Ksh <m>138,010</m> to have Ksh <m>400,000</m> in <m>18</m> years.</p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                An investor has <m>50,000</m> Shillings to save for <m>2</m> years. They are offered a nominal interest rate of <m>12 \%</m> per annum. Calculate and compare the total interest earned if the interest is
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Compounded Annually
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Compounded Semi-Annually
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> P = \amp \; \text{Ksh} \; 50,000</mrow>
                    <mrow> R = \amp 12 \;\text{%} </mrow>
                    <mrow> T = \amp 2 \; \text{years} </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                Applying the compound interest formula <m>A = P \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right) ^T</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           <md>
                                <mrow> A = \amp 50,000 \left(1 + \frac{12}{100}\right)^2 </mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp 50,000(1.12)^2 </mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp 62,720 \;\text{shillings} </mrow>
                           </md>
                            
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Interest is therefore equals <m>62,720 - 50,000 = 12,720 \;\text{shillings}</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            We adjust the rates to <m>R = \frac{12\;\text{%}}{2} = 6 \;\text{%} </m> and time to <m>4 \;\text{years}</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Applying the compound interest formula gives
                            <md>
                                <mrow> A = \amp \;50,000 \left(1 + \frac{6}{100}\right)^4</mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp \;50,000(1.006)^4 </mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp\; 63,123.85 \;\text{shillings} </mrow>
                            </md>
                            
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The interest compounded semi annually is <m>63,123.85 - 50,000 = 13,123.85 \;\text{shillings}</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                An entrepreneur wants to invest <m>100,000</m> Shillings for <m>1</m> year. They must choose between two competing bank offers. 
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           <alert>Bank A :</alert> Offers <m>12 \%</m> per annum compounded Quarterly.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <alert>Bank B :</alert> Offers <m>12.5 \%</m> per annum compounded Annually.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                Which one should he chose?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Adjust the rates <m>R = \frac{12 \;\text{%}}{4} = 3 \;\text{%}</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> A = \amp \;100,000(1+0.03)^4</mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp \; 112,550.88 \;\text{shillings}</mrow>
                            </md>
                            
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Interest earned <m> = 12,550.88 \;\text{shillings}</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> A = \amp \;100,000(1+0.125)^1</mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp \; 122,500 \;\text{shillings}</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Interest earned <m> = 12,500 \;\text{shillings}</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                Bank A; It yields a higher interest.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

